#1: Fear.  Frayed Knot booked Fear on an evening when Noble Blade was scheduled to kill Cazic Thule.  Frayed Knot cleared less than half of the plane before giving up for the evening, and Falconus negotiated to finish clearing the plane so that we could kill our mob.  Shissar spawns after we have nearly finished clearing the plane, and Frayed Knot states that they don't wish for Noble Blade to take Shissar, and that instead they would rather 'give' Shissar and Cazic to BOTS (To paraphrase a quote, 'We'd rather see BOTS take a mob than Noble Blade').  Noble Blade, instead of forcing our right to take the plane, left the plane with Shissar and Cazic Thule still up.  I believe (though at this point I may be incorrect) that BOTS moved in, helped you finish clearing, helped you kill Shissar, and then took Cazic as a FFA mob.  Did we stab you in the back here?  Did we steal a mob (Even when, by rights, we could have taken them as the plane was already released to us)?  Iniqy argues that he stipulated to Falconus that Noble Blade would not take Shissar, and I understand that's a case of one person's word against another, but when there was any shred of doubt, did Noble Blade not treat you fairly and leave the plane?<br>
<br>
#2: Sleeper's Tomb.  What's your resentment over this?  We had a rotation of four guilds in Sleeper's Tomb.   BOTS had long since gotten most everything they wanted from the zone.  SoT was only doing the zone when ShowEQ displayed the specific piece of primal that they wanted out of the zone.  Tindi had equipped the people they felt it was important to have primal.  Noble Blade maintained the rotation as best we could in the face of three other guilds not really caring about the zone, because in our guild we keep at something until everyone is equipped equally. When one of the other guilds asked for their turn, we stayed out of the zone. Frayed Knot begins killing mobs in Sleeper's.  When we noticed that that this was happening, we realized that there was finally interest in the zone and reinstated the rotation.  Frayed Knot has always had their turn at the rotation, and Noble Blade has never violated this.  Where in this situation does Frayed Knot find anything to resent Noble Blade about?<br>
<br>
#3: Dozekar.  As many as four guilds were on the Dozekar rotation before Frayed Knot ever entered ToV.  Of those four, none had ever even thought that the named drakes wouldn't be a part of the rotation.  Out of literally hundreds of people who were active in killing Dozekar and the named, it never occurred to us that we might take advantage of a 'loophole' and deny a fair shot at these quests to other guilds.  It wasn't until Frayed Knot (Admittedly among a few others) began their quest for Doze that the named drakes were put at risk.  Jurrasic stood forth and boldly stated that they intended to kill every named drake that they could. Why, then, are you surprised that Noble Blade would be shocked at such behavior?  We helped -build- the rotation system.  So the RTA hashed it out, clarified the rules and now everyone has their fair shot at Doze and the named mobs.  Yet FK resents Noble Blade for this?  Why?  Do you not get your fair shot at a full spawn?<br>
<br>
#4: Cazic Thule.  Every guild on the Rathe that has gotten onto the Cazic rotation has booked the plane on the day that they took Cazic.  It's common sense that you'll want plenty of time to try a new mob and that you'll not want to walk over the guild that has the plane reserved to do it.  We didn't have to write the rule down, because it was common sense.  If you can reserve a plane on the day the mob spawns, then isn't it easiest to secure your shot at the mob using that method?  The GM of the guild that had the plane reserved didn't release the plane to your guild, and from all indications Frayed Knot was rolling over a guild in their hurry to take a new mob.  While Cazic isn't a high priority to us, Karadin isn't going to stand by and allow that sort of impropriety to occur.  Once again, Noble Blade acted in the interest of the RTA, and you resent us for that?  <br>
<br>
#5: King Tormax.  You camped in the path of the guild that was up for Tormax.  You stalled that guild and then wiped out to the mob.  SoT then pulled the mob and killed it, after allowing you a fair shot at killing the mob.  Not only was there no foul here (You had your shot), but Noble Blade wasn't even involved!  Yet you cite this in your grievance against Noble Blade.  I find this odd, since Noble Blade most likely would have just left KT until you guys had cleared out and petitioned the RTA for an extra day.<br>
<br>
#6: Veeshan's Peak.  There is no rotation.  Nobody but Noble Blade has been stupid enough to want to do this zone.  When Frayed Knot wanted to clear VP, your GM spoke with Karadin (I didn't say 'asked permission'!  Don't get your feathers ruffled!) and both GM's made certain that there wouldn't be any conflict over the zone.  This is another example of Noble Blade backstabbing FK?<br>
<br>
I believe these are the six situations that people have cited in this thread.  Those are the specific grievances that Frayed Knot likes to hold up as examples of how they've been mistreated, yet in all six cases, I have just shown that you weren't mistreated at all.  I welcome... I challenge you to relieve me of my glaring ignorance regarding these situations.  Prove to me, not by niggling some minor point, but by addressing the overall situation, that my insight is incorrect, and I shall obligingly admit my own defeat.<br>
<br>
